"&#xa0;\nWritten evidence submitted by Mr Ron Hughes (CLC002)&#xa0;\nA summary of my main points\nA brief introduction\nFactual information I would like the committee to be aware of\nExtract from email 0942777075 dated  November 16, 1999:-\nPhil Jones to \nMichael\n Mann, and others, regarding a diagram for a World Meteorological Organization \n“I’ve just completed Mike’s Nature trick of adding in the real temperatures to each series for the last 20 years (i.e. from 1981 onwards) and from 1961 for Keith’s to \nhide the decline.” [My emphasis added]\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nExtract from email 1047474776 dated March 11, 2003\n:-\nPhil Jones replies to Michael Mann: “\nCan we not address the misconceptions by finally coming up with definitive dates for the Little Ice Age and Medieval Warm Period and redefining what we think the terms really mean? With all of us and more on the paper, it should carry a lot of weight. In a way we will be setting the agenda for what should be being done over the next few years.”\nApril 2013\n&#xa0;\n"